---
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Calculator logic and references for the TB Drug Dosage Calculator (Pyrazinamide and Ethambutol)."
    />
    <title>Calculator Logic and References – TB Drug Dosage Calculator</title>
  </head>
  <body class="bg-white text-gray-900 antialiased">
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-10">
      <p class="text-[15px]">
        <a class="text-blue-700 underline-offset-2 hover:underline" href="/">&larr; Back to the calculator</a>
      </p>

      <h1 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight">Calculator Logic and References</h1>

      <!-- Open-source callout -->
      <div class="mt-5 rounded-md border border-blue-200 bg-blue-50 px-4 py-3 text-[15px] font-semibold text-blue-900">
        This calculator is open source. The full code is on
        <a
          class="font-bold text-blue-700 underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-blue-800"
          href="https://github.com/Sephrael/tb-dosage-calculator"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener">GitHub</a
        > &mdash; contributions, corrections, and suggestions are very welcome.
      </div>

      <!-- Calculator Logic -->
      <p class="mt-6 text-[15px] font-bold">Calculator Logic</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-[15px] italic">
        **Recommended Rx and Ranges round up to closest available dosage, using scored tablet
        formulations available in US market.
      </p>

      <!-- Table 1: Pyrazinamide -->
      <div class="mt-5 overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full border-collapse text-[15px]">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-gray-100">
              <th class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold">
                Lean Body Weight(kg)
              </th>
              <th class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 text-center font-semibold">40&ndash;55</th>
              <th class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 text-center font-semibold">56&ndash;75</th>
              <th class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 text-center font-semibold">76&ndash;90</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2">Daily dosing</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 text-center">1000mg</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 text-center">1500mg</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 text-center">2000mg</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2">Three times a week dosing</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 text-center">1500mg</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 text-center">2500mg</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 text-center">3000mg</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-2 text-[15px] italic">
        Suggested Pyrazinamide Dosing (IF CrCl &gt;30). Adapted from ATS/CDC/IDSA 2016 clinical
        practice guidelines for treatment of drug-susceptible tuberculosis.
      </p>

      <!-- Table 2: Ethambutol -->
      <div class="mt-5 overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full border-collapse text-[15px]">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-gray-100">
              <th class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold">
                Lean Body Weight(kg)
              </th>
              <th class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 text-center font-semibold">40&ndash;55</th>
              <th class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 text-center font-semibold">56&ndash;75</th>
              <th class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 text-center font-semibold">76&ndash;90</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2">Daily Dosing</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 text-center">800mg</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 text-center">1200mg</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 text-center">1600mg</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2">Three times weekly dosing</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 text-center">1200mg</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 text-center">2000mg</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 text-center">2400mg</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-2 text-[15px] italic">
        Suggested Ethambutol Dosing (IF CrCl &gt;30). Adapted from ATS/CDC/IDSA 2016 clinical practice
        guidelines for treatment of drug-susceptible tuberculosis.
      </p>

      <!-- Overall dose ranges -->
      <p class="mt-6 text-[15px]">
        Overall Dose Ranges for PZA: 18.2-26.8mg/kg(max 2000mg)<br />
        Overall Dose Ranges for EMB: 14.5-21.4mg/kg(max 1600mg)<br />
        If CrCl &gt;30, NOT receiving renal replacement therapy, and LBW 40-90, then dosing as per
        tables above.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-5 text-[15px]">
        If CrCl &gt;30, NOT receiving renal replacement therapy, and LBW &lt; 40 then PZA 20mg/kg and
        EMB 15mg/kg<br />
        Dose Range PZA: 20-25mg/kg(max 2000mg)<br />
        Dose Range EMB: 15-20mg/kg(max 1600mg)
      </p>

      <p class="mt-5 text-[15px]">
        If CrCl &lt; 30 OR receiving renal replacement therapy then PZA ~30mg/kg and EMB 15mg/kg with
        dose frequency as described on main page<br />
        Dose Range PZA: 25-35mg/kg(max 2000mg)<br />
        Dose Range EMB: 15-25mg/kg(max 1600mg)
      </p>

      <!-- Equations & references -->
      <ul class="mt-6 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-[15px]">
        <li>
          James Equation for Lean Body Mass Calculation:
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
            <li>Male Lean Body Mass (kg) = (1.1 * wtKg) - 128 * (wtKg/htCm)^2</li>
            <li>Female Lean Body Mass (kg) = (1.07 * wtKg) - 148 * (wtKg/htCm)^2</li>
            <li>
              As described in the poster
              <a
                class="text-blue-700 underline-offset-2 hover:underline"
                href="http://muirheads.co.uk/richard/RM_poster.pdf">here</a
              >, the James Equation arrives at a local maximum above a male BMI of 43 and female BMI
              of 36.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          Cockcroft-Gault Equation
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
            <li>CrCl(mL/min) = (140 &ndash; age) &times; (weight, kg) &times; (0.85 if female) / (72 &times; Cr)</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          Dosing of PZA and EMB by weight bands in adults with normal renal function:
          <a
            class="break-all text-blue-700 underline-offset-2 hover:underline"
            href="https://www.idsociety.org/practice-guideline/treatment-of-drug-susceptible-tb/"
            >https://www.idsociety.org/practice-guideline/treatment-of-drug-susceptible-tb/</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          Dosing of PZA and EMB in adults with renal insufficiency/failure:
          <a
            class="break-all text-blue-700 underline-offset-2 hover:underline"
            href="https://www.currytbcenter.ucsf.edu/sites/default/files/tb_sg3_chap7_co-morbidities.pdf#renalfailure"
            >https://www.currytbcenter.ucsf.edu/sites/default/files/tb_sg3_chap7_co-morbidities.pdf#renalfailure</a
          >
        </li>
      </ul>

      <hr class="mx-auto my-8 w-40 border-gray-200" />
      <p class="text-[15px]">
        <a class="text-blue-700 underline-offset-2 hover:underline" href="/">&larr; Back to the calculator</a>
      </p>
    </main>

    <footer class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-8 text-xs text-gray-500">
      TB Drug Dosage Calculator
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
